Samsung Wins $100 Million Contract From Saudi Venture, MEED Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-04-17T13:43:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/samsung-wins-100-million-contract-from-saudi-venture-meed-says.html
Samsung Engineering Ltd. won a $100
million contract from a joint venture between Saudi Arabian
Mining Co. and  Alcoa Inc (AA)  to develop facilities at a smelter
project in Ras Al Zour in  Saudi Arabia ,  MEED  reported, citing an
unidentified person familiar with the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  